author: The Current
description:
To celebrate The Current’s 20th Anniversary, The Current’s Live Sessions Vault unlocks never-before-seen live performance videos of bands and artists who have played in our iconic studio. 

Watch to see the full session of The Jayhawks, featuring previously unreleased footage, from when they visited the The Current studio back in 2014.

Songs Performed 
00:00:00 The Man Who Loved Life
00:04:26 Queen of the World
00:06:59 Stumbling Through the Dark
00:09:21 Tailspin

Musicians
Gary Louris – vocals, guitar
Jon Jackson – mandolin
Marc Perlman – bass
Jessey Green – violin
Karen Grotberg – piano
Kraig Johnson – guitar
Tim O’Reagan — drums

Credits
Engineer – Mike DeMark
Producer – Jade
Visuals  – Nate Ryan
Digital Producer – Natalia Toledo
Graphics – Natalia Toledo

The Current’s Live Sessions Vault is supported by the Minnesota Orchestra, GS Motors, and Delta Dental of Minnesota Foundation.
